text=!!How InfoCodex integrates with Microsoft Sharepoint-Portal%0a%0aWe are preparing an interface for the integration of InfoCodex into MS [[http://office.microsoft.com/en-us/FX010909721033.aspx | SharepointPortal]].%0a%0a!!!Basic Technologies%0a# Using WebParts on the SharePoint Portal side for customizing the SharePoint application (standard used by MS SharePoint)%0a# Using the SOAP protocol (packages of XML statements) for the information exchange between SharePoint and InfoCodex (standard used by MS SharePoint)%0a# '''Providing the InfoCodex API in the form of Web Services (standard used by MS SharePoint)''' This item is presumably the most important step, and this part is ready now.%0a%0a!!!Demo of the InfoCodex Web Services%0aWe have prepared a demo version of the Web Services on our new demo server (real searches on real collections; not just a dummy).%0a %0a!!!Start URL %0ahttp://demo.infocodex.com/webservicetest/icwstst.aspx%0a%0aIn the start page you can see how the InfoCodex Web Services are called. %0aThe answers of the InfoCodex API to your requests are formally presented %0ain the form of XML streams.%0a%0aThe [[http://demo.infocodex.com/webservicetest/WebService-scheme.pdf | general scheme]] can be viewed on a PDF file (the link appears on the start page as well).
